description:
Partners in Health, a contact tracing company, lists both George Soros’ Open Society Foundation and the Bill and Melinda Gates Foundation as official partners and supporters who contributed $1 million or more, according to a 2015 annual report. •

Chelsea Clinton serves on Partners in Health’s Board of Trustees. Partners in Health was founded by Jim Kim, who is now the president of the UN World Bank and Paul Farmer, whose health programs have been funded in the past by Soros. •
Democrat Representative Bobby Rush introduced HR 6666, the COVID-19 TRACE Act, that authorizes the federal government to grant approved entities the right to conduct contact tracing for coronavirus at “individuals’ residences.” Contact tracing involves investigators tracing every interaction that infected people have. •
